column1: How well do your colleagues at school understand you as a person?
column2: How connected do you feel to other adults at your school?
column3: How respected do you feel around other colleagues at your school?
column4: Overall, how much do you feel like you are accepted at your school?
column5: How easy is it to interact with students at your school who have different backgrounds from your own?
column6: If students with different backgrounds struggled to get along in your class, how comfortable would you be intervening?
column7: How comfortable would you be having conversations about race and gender with your students?
column8: When a sensitive issue of diversity arises in class, how easily can you use strategies to address the situation?
column9: How confident are you that you can - engage students who struggle with motivation
column10: How confident are you that you can - help your school's most challenging students to learn
column11: How confident are you that you can - support your students' growth in developing empathy?
column12: How confident are you that you can - support your students' growth in developing self-awareness?
column13: How confident are you that you can - support your students' growth in developing self-management?
column14: How often do you see students helping each other without being prompted?
column15: How respectful are the relationships between staff and students?
column16: How supportive are the attitudes of your colleagues towards each other?
column17: Overall, how supportive is the working environment at your school?
